"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-snoop-dogg-olympic-torch-opening-ceremony-paris\", \"text\": \"American rapper Snoop Dogg will be lighting up during the upcoming 2024 Olympic Games in Paris. Lighting up as in carrying the iconic Olympic torch, of course.  The 52-year-old Snoop Dogg was chosen to hoist the Olympic torch in the final stretch leading up to the opening ceremony Friday night in Paris. Mathieu Hanotin, the mayor of Saint-Denis\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a suburb of northern Paris that is the home of the Stade de France Olympic Stadium\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094announced the decision on social media.  \\\"Saint Denis: last step before the Eiffel Tower. An international cast [Snoop Dogg] for the last stretch of the Olympic flame,\\\" Hanotinsaid in the post, translated to English.  Snoop Dogg confirmed the news on social media Tuesday.  U gots to do it!! \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u008a\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u00bf\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ba\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b8\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00a5\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u0083\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008f\\u00bf\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ab\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00b7 Will u be watchin??#FollowTheDogg#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/3l12Cj74Cp  Joining Snoop Dogg as Olympic torchbearers in Saint-Denis include French actress Laetitia Casta and rapper MC Solaar.  The final torchbearer who will light the Olympic cauldron to begin the opening ceremony has yet to be announced.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Tom Dierberger is the Deputy News Director at Sports Illustrated. He joined SI in November 2023 after stints at FOX Sports, Bally Sports and NBC Sports. Dierberger has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in communication from St. John\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s University. In his spare time, he can be seen throwing out his arm while playing fetch with his dog, Walter B. Boy.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTE